# Modifying LeRobot Source

This repo is a fork of huggingface/lerobot. Files under `src/lerobot/` come from upstream and are periodically synced via `git merge upstream/main`.

## Before editing

- Check if the change can be done in a custom file (under `scripts/`, `configs/`, or `Makefile`) instead of modifying upstream source. Additive files never cause merge conflicts.
- If you must modify upstream source, keep changes minimal and well-isolated.

## Currently modified upstream files

- `src/lerobot/scripts/lerobot_record.py` -- progress bar, action debug logging, headless fixes
- `src/lerobot/utils/control_utils.py` -- stdin-based headless keyboard controls

See `ledream_changelog.md` section "Modified Upstream Files" for details.

## When modifying upstream files

- Mark custom code blocks with `# DP:` comments so they're easy to find during merge conflict resolution
- Add a brief entry to `ledream_changelog.md` under the file's section
- Prefer appending new functions over modifying existing upstream functions
- If modifying an existing upstream function, keep the diff as small as possible
